gram-for-android-191600004.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/meta-launches-a-threads-beta-program-for-android-191600004.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 066f942f-6f05-4060-9429-091b69b2f65c</guid><dc:creator>威尔·尚克林</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jul 2023 19:16:00 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688757361</ingested><modified> 2023-07-07T19:16:05+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Will Shanklin]]></category><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/f2dfbb80-1cf8-11ee-b1ff-53448d46dc64" width="6000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4000" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/f2dfbb80-1cf8-11ee-b1ff-53448d46dc64" width="6000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NurPhoto via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[A girl looks at a Threads app at the Play Store on July 7, 2023, in Colombo, Sri Lanka. (Photo by Thilina Kaluthotage/NurPhoto via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Instagram Launches An App To Rival Twitter]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Canadian judge rules the thumbs up emoji counts as a contract agreement]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>加拿大法官裁定，流行的“竖起大拇指”表情符号不仅可以用作合同协议，而且与实际签名一样有效。 <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/06/canada-judge-thumbs-up-emoji-sign-contract">正如<em><ins>《卫报》</ins></em><ins>最初报道的那样，</ins>萨斯喀彻温省的法官做出这一裁决的理由是，法院必须适应人们沟通方式的“新现实”。</a></p><p>该案涉及一名谷物买家群发短信招揽客户，一名农民同意以每蒲式耳 13 美元左右的价格出售 86 吨亚麻。买方向农民发送了一份合同协议，并要求农民“确认”收到合同。他在收到文件时发出了竖起大拇指的表情符号，但在亚麻价格上涨后退出了交易。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>买方起诉了农民，称竖起大拇指不仅仅代表收到了合同。它代表着对合同条件的同意，法官也同意了，并命令农民支付近 62,000 美元，这可能会导致一系列呕吐表情符号。</p><p>农场主克里斯·阿赫特 (Chris Achter) 在一份宣誓书中表示，他“没有时间审查”合同，竖起大拇指只是确认收到。蒂莫西·基恩法官依据的是<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.dictionary.com/e/emoji/thumbs-up-emoji/"><ins>Dictionary.com 对表情符号的定义，</ins></a>该定义指出该图像用于“在数字通信中表达同意、认可或鼓励，特别是在西方文化中”，最终站在了谷物买家一边。</p><p> “本法院欣然承认👍表情符号是‘签署’文件的非传统方式，但尽管如此，在这种情况下，这是传达‘签名’两个目的的有效方式，”基恩法官写道。</p><p>辩方认为，赋予表情符号这种权力将为增强对其他表情符号的解释打开“闸门”。虽然法官驳回了这一推理，但任何经常发 LOL 表情符号但实际上没有笑出声的人现在可能会感到浑身发抖。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/canadian-judge-rules-the-thumbs-up-emoji-counts-as-a-contract-agreement-190026176.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/canadian-judge-rules-the-thumbs-up-emoji-counts-as-a-contract-agreement-190026176.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 4ad33e1a-e248-4eea-9a10-43bf8d75af41</guid><dc:creator>劳伦斯·邦克</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 07 Jul 2023 19:00:26 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1688755358</ingested><modified> 2023-07-07T18:42:42+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Company Legal & Law Matters]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Lawrence Bonk]]></category><medi